<div><h3>GAME 275 - Character Animation </h3>  <hr>Animated characters are becoming increasingly popular as pivotal assets in animation, storytelling, and simulation related industries. The fundamentals of creating animation lie in the ability to generate believable characters that have emotion and life. This course will explore tools and techniques used in the animation industry to design convincing character animations including blocking, breakdowns, non-linear, and procedural animation.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> GAME 230<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Fall<br><br></div>		</td>
